<SampleDescription>
    <p>This sample demonstrates how to digitally sign a PDF document programmatically using Syncfusion's <strong>SfPdfViewer</strong> and PDF Library. It illustrates adding a digital signature from code-behind and reloading the signed document in the viewer.</p>
</SampleDescription>

<ActionDescription>
    <p>This sample requires at least one signature field in the PDF document. When all signature fields are signed, the "Finish Signing" button is enabled. Selecting this button programmatically applies a digital signature certificate and reloads the signed document in the viewer.</p>

    <br />

    <p>The following messages are displayed based on the validation results:</p>

    <br />

    <ul>
        <li>
            <p><strong>Document modified after signing</strong>: The document has been digitally signed, but it has been modified since it was signed, and at least one signature is invalid.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Shown if the digitally signed document is edited after reloading.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p><strong>Signature has a problem</strong>: The document has been digitally signed, and at least one signature has a problem.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Displayed when the digital signature certificate is not registered on the machine and is not in the trusted list. Add the certificate to the trusted list to resolve this.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p><strong>All signatures are valid</strong>: The document has been digitally signed, and all signatures are valid.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Indicates the document is signed without any issues.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

